WEBVTT

00:00.551 --> 00:02.218
<i>So here's what you missed</i>
<i>on</i> Glee: <i> Sue got fired</i>

00:02.252 --> 00:03.719
<i>from McKinley, so now she's</i>

00:03.754 --> 00:05.421
<i>at Carmel High
coaching Vocal Adrenaline.</i>

00:05.456 --> 00:07.356
<i>Dalton Academy burnt down,
and all the Warblers</i>

00:07.391 --> 00:09.192
<i>came to McKinley, which is good
because the New Directions!</i>

00:09.226 --> 00:10.860
<i>Didn't have enough kids,
and if they don't win,</i>

00:10.894 --> 00:12.695
<i>the glee club's over,
but it might be anyway</i>

00:12.730 --> 00:14.263
<i>because Rachel got
accepted back at NYADA</i>

00:14.298 --> 00:15.932
<i>and got offered
a role on Broadway.</i>

00:15.966 --> 00:17.926
<i>And that's what you missed</i>
<i>on</i> Glee.

00:20.178 --> 00:22.012
All right, I don't care
what the body's doing.

00:22.046 --> 00:24.181
Just make sure the <i> facce</i>
is doing something special.

00:24.215 --> 00:26.516
A five, six, seven, eight.

00:26.551 --> 00:28.719
Show it. Hide it.

00:28.753 --> 00:30.854
Hit your friend,
hit your friend.

00:30.888 --> 00:33.724
- Grab the jelly... - Good, you guys.
Remember, show faces.

00:33.758 --> 00:36.526
Make a sandwich, throw it down.
Stay at home, stay at home.

00:36.561 --> 00:38.328
Leave your home, seven, eight.

00:38.363 --> 00:40.497
Twinkle, twinkle, little star.

00:40.531 --> 00:42.933
Mother, may I point to you?

00:42.967 --> 00:45.002
- All right, not bad, guys.
- Yay! That was so good, you guys!

00:45.036 --> 00:46.236
Let's take five.

00:46.270 --> 00:48.238
Uh, no, no, no.
Let's not take five.

00:48.272 --> 00:50.674
- Excuse me? - My feet are like
an outtake from <i> Black Swan,</i>

00:50.708 --> 00:53.010
but you don't hear me
complaining...

00:53.044 --> 00:55.846
Because my fellow Warblers and I
understand the stakes involved.

00:55.880 --> 00:58.360
May I remind you that if
we don't win sectionals,

00:58.383 --> 01:00.884
Glee Club no longer exists.

01:00.918 --> 01:02.386
Do you think
Sue Sylvester is giving

01:02.420 --> 01:04.888
Vocal Adrenaline
a five minute break? No.

01:04.922 --> 01:07.924
This weekend, I saw them
walking on hot coals.

01:07.959 --> 01:09.960
(all screaming)

01:11.396 --> 01:13.797
If Oprah can do this,
so can you.

01:17.001 --> 01:18.735
- We suck!
- Okay, you suck!

01:18.770 --> 01:20.470
Take a nap, Nickelodeon.

01:20.505 --> 01:21.938
(all arguing indistinctly)

01:21.973 --> 01:24.041
- Relax.
- KURT: Come on, guys.

01:24.075 --> 01:25.809
Everyone's improving
very nicely.

01:25.843 --> 01:27.878
This is not the time to panic.

01:27.912 --> 01:29.713
But it is time to be pragmatic.

01:29.747 --> 01:31.615
With all due respect
to our well-meaning teachers,

01:31.649 --> 01:34.584
there is zero chance
of beating Vocal Adrenaline

01:34.619 --> 01:37.554
with rudimentary moves like
"Mother, may I point

01:37.588 --> 01:38.722
to you?"

01:38.756 --> 01:40.223
- I love that move.
- It's awesome.

01:40.258 --> 01:42.259
- Thank you.
- Moreover, the Warblers and I

01:42.293 --> 01:44.394
recently had a little sidebar,
and we believe it's time

01:44.429 --> 01:46.964
for a frank discussion about
who should be featured up front.

01:46.998 --> 01:48.665
And who should be...

01:48.700 --> 01:50.100
- hidden in the back.
- JANE: No.

01:50.134 --> 01:51.802
The only three girls
in this group

01:51.836 --> 01:53.070
are not moving to the back.

01:53.104 --> 01:54.504
Nope.

01:54.539 --> 01:56.073
- Uh-uh.
- Oh, no, no, no.

01:56.107 --> 01:57.274
I wasn't talking
about the girls.

01:57.308 --> 01:59.476
I was talking about...

01:59.510 --> 02:01.078
Just say it, Skyler.

02:01.112 --> 02:02.980
The dead weight.

02:03.014 --> 02:05.494
Look, we all know that some of
us aren't as physically fit

02:05.516 --> 02:08.018
as others, but give
Roderick some time.

02:08.051 --> 02:10.320
He's got a killer voice
and he's a quick learner.

02:10.354 --> 02:12.189
I guarantee he can get
the dance moves, dude.

02:12.223 --> 02:13.290
And when will you
get them, dude?

02:13.324 --> 02:14.524
You're just as bad as he is.

02:14.559 --> 02:15.592
You're worse!

02:15.627 --> 02:17.260
You dance like a blind man

02:17.295 --> 02:18.762
with a back brace
who hasn't taken

02:18.796 --> 02:20.530
a dump in three weeks!

02:20.565 --> 02:21.865
Hey, I don't have to dance good.

02:21.899 --> 02:23.267
I just need to look good,
and I do.

02:23.301 --> 02:24.501
Get over yourself!

02:24.535 --> 02:26.169
We all look good.

02:26.204 --> 02:28.105
Even Julianne Moore over there.

02:28.139 --> 02:29.640
Order, order, gentlemen.
What?

02:29.674 --> 02:32.276
Look, I have to agree
with super gay Warbler.

02:32.310 --> 02:35.279
I love you guys, but we
just can't afford to lose.

02:35.313 --> 02:37.915
So, unless you magically get
better, like, this second,

02:37.949 --> 02:39.349
then I think you should

02:39.384 --> 02:41.384
take one for the team
and maybe just...

02:41.386 --> 02:43.186
stay hidden in the back row.

