02:56.935 --> 02:58.302
- You okay?
- Yeah, I'm...

02:58.336 --> 02:59.670
I'm fine.

02:59.704 --> 03:00.737
No, you're a mess.

03:00.772 --> 03:02.639
Let me help you with that.

03:02.674 --> 03:04.741
Thanks.

03:04.776 --> 03:06.977
How the hell are we supposed
to get this routine down

03:07.011 --> 03:08.545
if I can't even
get through my day

03:08.580 --> 03:10.013
without tripping over myself?

03:10.048 --> 03:11.548
We're screwed.

03:11.583 --> 03:13.584
I feel like a hippo
trying to do ballet

03:13.618 --> 03:16.420
like some strange nightmare
out of <i> Fantasia.</i>

03:16.454 --> 03:18.355
I know, man. I got
moves on the field,

03:18.389 --> 03:20.357
but I can't seem to get these
dance moves down. It's...

03:20.391 --> 03:22.326
right, left,
right, left... Yeah?

03:22.360 --> 03:23.894
No, I thought it was
left and then right.

03:23.928 --> 03:25.696
Well... I don't know.

03:25.730 --> 03:27.164
I mean, how are we supposed
to get through this routine

03:27.198 --> 03:28.532
if neither one of us
actually even knows it?

03:28.566 --> 03:29.600
I mean, we need
someone to help us.

03:29.634 --> 03:31.034
- Maybe Alistair can...
- No.

03:31.069 --> 03:32.536
No, I'm sorry.
I just don't want

03:32.570 --> 03:34.171
- to watch you two make
out all weekend. - Yeah.

03:34.205 --> 03:36.039
But we got to have someone
to whip us into shape.

03:36.074 --> 03:37.274
Well, how about Mr. Shue, then?

03:37.308 --> 03:38.675
He's the best dancer.

03:38.710 --> 03:40.677
We need his moves,
but he'll just

03:40.712 --> 03:43.113
tell us he's proud of us even
when we're doing a subpar job.

03:43.147 --> 03:44.414
Who we really need...

03:44.449 --> 03:45.849
- is Kitty.
- Is Kitty.

03:45.884 --> 03:47.784
I mean, she's by far
our harshest critic.

03:47.819 --> 03:49.086
And a true taskmaster.

03:49.120 --> 03:50.420
She'll make at least
one of us cry.

03:50.455 --> 03:51.889
Yeah.

03:51.923 --> 03:53.223
I'll see you later.
(school bell rings)

03:53.258 --> 03:54.525
Want to do that.

03:54.559 --> 03:56.393
And try this one second.

03:56.427 --> 03:58.595
Hey, uh, Rachel, do you have
a second to go over this list?

03:58.630 --> 04:00.297
I-I-I thought that Kurt

04:00.331 --> 04:02.533
- had the set list for sectionals
nailed down. - Uh, yeah.

04:02.567 --> 04:04.034
No, this is a list of performers

04:04.068 --> 04:05.802
that, uh, finished
their college degrees

04:05.837 --> 04:07.371
before they actually...

04:07.405 --> 04:09.406
Sam...
jumped to Broadway or Hollywood.

04:09.440 --> 04:10.874
We talked about this, okay?
You were very clear

04:10.909 --> 04:11.975
