and I'm very clear

04:12.010 --> 04:13.076
about how I feel.

04:13.111 --> 04:14.912
Patti LuPone, Carrie Underwood,

04:14.946 --> 04:17.147
- Meryl Streep.
- Okay, look. You know what?

04:17.182 --> 04:19.249
I knew you were gonna do this,
so I made a list of all

04:19.284 --> 04:20.983
the performers who either
dropped out of college

04:21.019 --> 04:23.287
or who didn't go at all, and
who had very successful careers.

04:23.321 --> 04:25.055
Here you go... Lady
Gaga, Coco Chanel

04:25.089 --> 04:27.224
and Miss Barbra
Streisand herself.

04:27.258 --> 04:29.259
I know you, so I made
this list of people

04:29.294 --> 04:31.461
that dropped out
and were huge for five minutes,

04:31.496 --> 04:32.963
but then were
never heard of again.

04:32.997 --> 04:34.832
Kesha.

04:34.866 --> 04:36.900
- Kesha's still performing.
- Okay, well, my bad. I'm just...

04:36.935 --> 04:38.469
Sam, please, look.

04:38.503 --> 04:40.270
I hear you, okay?

04:40.305 --> 04:42.272
And you're being a
really good friend.

04:42.307 --> 04:44.408
I just... I don't want to
talk about this anymore

04:44.442 --> 04:47.311
unless you support
my choice, okay?

04:47.345 --> 04:48.812
All right.

04:48.847 --> 04:51.615
You know...

04:51.649 --> 04:53.350
we all support you.

04:53.384 --> 04:54.785
Okay, we always do.

04:54.819 --> 04:57.821
Just please, think
about the future, okay?

04:57.856 --> 04:59.123
And not just, like,
the next month

04:59.157 --> 05:00.691
or the next big
ticket out of here,

05:00.725 --> 05:02.359
but actually look
back at yourself

05:02.393 --> 05:03.994
from the future and ask

05:04.028 --> 05:06.530
