(cracks) (groaning)

10:37.829 --> 10:40.698
(sighing, groaning) Aw, gross.

10:40.732 --> 10:42.299
Holy crow!

10:42.334 --> 10:43.634
You did a number on this thing.

10:43.668 --> 10:45.028
Geez, it looks like
somebody rubbed

10:45.036 --> 10:47.004
beets all over your feet.
I love beets.

10:47.038 --> 10:48.506
The X-rays were negative.
It's just a sprain.

10:48.540 --> 10:50.140
But it's one of the
worst I've ever seen.

10:50.141 --> 10:52.810
It's fine, and I'm
not missing sectionals.

10:52.844 --> 10:54.512
The only way you could put
weight on that thing,

10:54.546 --> 10:56.313
let alone dance,
is if you got a cortisone shot.

10:56.348 --> 10:58.449
Okay.
Well, it'll take away the pain,

10:58.483 --> 11:01.218
but it won't fix the damage.
Damage?

11:01.253 --> 11:03.154
I've read this book before, son.

11:03.188 --> 11:04.889
It's a book written
by these knees.

11:04.923 --> 11:06.524
Looks like
a jacked up C-section.

11:06.558 --> 11:08.225
If you perform
on an ankle like that,

11:08.260 --> 11:09.994
there's no telling
how much worse it'll get.

11:10.028 --> 11:12.196
Torn ligaments,
ruptured tendons.

11:12.230 --> 11:15.166
You take an injury that should
take two weeks to heal,

11:15.200 --> 11:18.335
and you turn it into a month,
a year, maybe never.

11:18.370 --> 11:20.204
I-I've heard enough.
This is insane.

11:20.238 --> 11:21.572
Absolutely not.

11:21.606 --> 11:22.973
There's no way
I can let you perform.

11:23.008 --> 11:24.041
No, it's worth it.

11:24.075 --> 11:25.176
No, Spencer, listen to him.

11:25.210 --> 11:27.244
Look, I'm not the best dancer,

11:27.279 --> 11:28.579
I'm not the best singer,

