30:06.649 --> 30:10.218
♪ Come sail away with me. ♪

30:10.252 --> 30:12.720
(crowd cheering)

30:28.237 --> 30:30.205
(cheering, excited chatter)

30:34.355 --> 30:35.422
(school bell ringing)

30:35.456 --> 30:37.057
Can I just say, I can't believe

30:37.091 --> 30:38.992
I got roped into
doing this thing again...

30:39.027 --> 30:41.995
What has got to be
the lowest form of entertainment

30:42.030 --> 30:43.363
ever known to mankind.

30:43.672 --> 30:45.213
__

30:45.333 --> 30:47.567
So when I got the call
this morning, I'm like,

30:47.602 --> 30:50.404
"Okay, Donna Landries,
just calm down.

30:50.438 --> 30:54.274
These groups cannot be worse
than the last time."

30:54.308 --> 30:56.677
And then they were.

30:56.711 --> 30:58.578
I don't know which group
I hated more.

30:58.613 --> 30:59.813
The Vocal Adrenalines
were like...

30:59.847 --> 31:02.015
that was like
sitting through Fallujah.

31:02.050 --> 31:03.784
You gonna point a cannon at me?

31:03.818 --> 31:05.419
Hell no!

31:05.453 --> 31:07.688
And what's up with
this bird school?

31:07.722 --> 31:09.589
I-Is that a public school?

31:09.624 --> 31:12.759
Is that where
my taxpayer dollars are going?

31:12.794 --> 31:14.961
And don't start me
on New Directions! Oh!

31:14.996 --> 31:17.130
Now, Donna, I'm gonna
stop you right there.

31:17.165 --> 31:19.366
They might not be able
to dance or sing,

31:19.400 --> 31:21.201
but when it comes
to New Directions!

31:21.235 --> 31:23.637
Of the female persuasion, ooh.

31:23.849 --> 31:25.353
__

31:25.473 --> 31:27.140
I mean, how about
that smoking gal

31:27.175 --> 31:29.443
going Au naturel
with the Pam Grier Afro?

31:29.477 --> 31:32.012
Sister's got it going on.

31:32.046 --> 31:34.715
She got me hankering for
a piping hot cup o' cocoa.

31:34.749 --> 31:37.050
What the hell
did you just say to me?

31:37.085 --> 31:39.565
Technically, I'm not even
supposed to be judging.

31:39.685 --> 31:41.269
__

31:41.389 --> 31:43.657
The invitation was
addressed to Trixie,

31:43.691 --> 31:45.125
so really it's up to the dog.

31:45.159 --> 31:47.227
(barks)

31:47.261 --> 31:49.830
Sorry. Trixie's
not racist.

31:49.864 --> 31:52.366
Like all dogs, he sees
in black and white,

31:52.400 --> 31:54.468
and darker skin makes
it harder for him

31:54.502 --> 31:56.982
to make out facial features.

31:57.005 --> 31:58.672
Wait, this dog is a dude?

31:58.706 --> 32:00.307
BUTCH:
He sure is.

32:00.341 --> 32:02.509
And that maleness might
just give us an indication

32:02.543 --> 32:04.177
as to how he's gonna vote.

32:04.212 --> 32:05.646
Now, Trixie...
(clicker clicks)

32:05.680 --> 32:07.314
Trixie, Trixie.

32:07.348 --> 32:11.051
Which glee club displayed
more... "performativity"?

32:11.085 --> 32:12.285
Good boy!

32:12.320 --> 32:14.021
Are you out of your mind?

32:14.055 --> 32:16.423
That was the worst music
I've ever heard.

32:16.457 --> 32:19.726
There's not a single person on
Earth who woke up this morning

32:19.761 --> 32:22.663
and said, "You know what song I
just really need to hear today?"

32:22.697 --> 32:23.764
'Hey, Mickey.'"

32:23.798 --> 32:25.365
And by the time
fatty was singing.

32:25.400 --> 32:27.701
"Take Me to the Church,"
I'm like, "Okay.

32:27.735 --> 32:30.437
Provided the service we attend
is my funeral."

32:30.471 --> 32:33.573
Well, I thought I knew
which show choir had my vote.

32:33.608 --> 32:35.709
But as I scour

32:35.743 --> 32:37.611
the depths of my soul,

32:37.645 --> 32:41.581
I now realize
I have deep reservations

32:41.616 --> 32:44.084
about sending them to regionals.

32:44.118 --> 32:45.585
Well, can we just vote, please?

32:45.620 --> 32:47.554
I got piles.

32:49.490 --> 32:51.358
(school bell ringing)

32:51.392 --> 32:53.060
ANNOUNCER: Before we get
to announcing the winners,

32:53.094 --> 32:54.795
a quick message
from our sponsor:

32:54.829 --> 32:57.764
Wayne's Waffle House is where
to spend your Sundays.

32:57.799 --> 32:59.433
(applause)

33:01.736 --> 33:03.536
(whispering):
I love waffles.

33:04.739 --> 33:06.659
ANNOUNCER:
And now, in third place...

33:11.512 --> 33:13.447
...from the John James
Audubon Institute

33:13.481 --> 33:16.483
for Rehabilitative Ornithology,
the Falconers!

33:20.688 --> 33:23.457
And now, without further ado...

33:23.491 --> 33:27.928
the winner of this year's
sectionals is...

33:41.976 --> 33:43.944
...the New Directions!

33:43.978 --> 33:47.180
(cheering)

33:47.215 --> 33:49.650
♪ ♪

34:15.877 --> 34:17.878
♪ ♪

34:26.460 --> 34:29.496
All right, guys. We're back
at it on Monday morning.

34:29.530 --> 34:30.764
(sighs)

34:30.797 --> 34:32.466
SUE:
Hello, William.

34:36.437 --> 34:39.072
Well, Sue,

34:39.107 --> 34:41.208
looks like it finally happened.

34:41.242 --> 34:42.909
You lost.

34:42.944 --> 34:45.579
Yeah, in a manner
of speaking, yes.

34:45.612 --> 34:47.714
And I have only one thing
to say to you,

34:47.748 --> 34:49.916
and one thing only:
You're welcome.

34:51.219 --> 34:52.585
(chuckles)
I didn't say thank you.

34:52.620 --> 34:54.621
I know, and that's
just plain rude,

34:54.655 --> 34:58.191
because I handed your glee club
a victory on a silver platter,

34:58.226 --> 34:59.693
guaranteeing that
the New Directions!

34:59.727 --> 35:01.895
Will be a part of this school

35:01.929 --> 35:03.397
long after you and I are gone.

35:03.431 --> 35:05.098
Okay, what are you
talking about?

35:05.133 --> 35:07.213
You've spent the last six years
trying to destroy us.

35:07.235 --> 35:09.269
Now you want me to believe
that you suddenly had

35:09.303 --> 35:11.423
a change of heart and you've
been secretly helping us?

35:11.439 --> 35:12.973
Well, that's exactly
what happened,

35:13.007 --> 35:15.309
and I am impressed
that a mind as simple as yours

35:15.343 --> 35:17.110
could make that sophisticated
leap in logic.

35:17.145 --> 35:18.979
What are you talking about?

35:19.013 --> 35:21.915
Well, it is true that I have
spent a better part of a decade

35:21.949 --> 35:23.750
trying to destroy you
and the glee club,

35:23.785 --> 35:26.119
for which I harbor a deep
and abiding hatred,

35:26.154 --> 35:29.556
but when that backstabbing
Geraldo Rivera,

35:29.590 --> 35:32.459
with his craven
ad hominem hack job...

35:32.493 --> 35:35.329
there were only two people
who stood up for me:

35:35.363 --> 35:38.065
Coach Sheldon "The
Abomination" Beiste

35:38.099 --> 35:39.466
and you.

35:39.500 --> 35:41.068
So I took it upon myself

35:41.102 --> 35:42.803
to repay you by sabotaging.

35:42.837 --> 35:45.172
Vocal Adrenaline
from the inside,

35:45.206 --> 35:47.274
handing you a win at sectionals.

35:47.308 --> 35:48.775
Okay, that is insane.

35:48.810 --> 35:50.811
You were absolutely trying
to win today.

35:50.845 --> 35:52.679
You pulled out all the stops.

35:52.714 --> 35:54.181
That was, by far,

35:54.215 --> 35:55.782
the most over-the-top routine.

35:55.817 --> 35:57.517
Vocal Adrenaline has ever done.

35:57.552 --> 35:59.620
Precisely, and it was a routine

35:59.654 --> 36:02.122
specifically tailored
to the deep background

36:02.156 --> 36:04.324
I performed on all three judges.

36:04.359 --> 36:06.259
Now, I knew that an
overly produced,

36:06.294 --> 36:10.330
acrobatic spectacle would remind
Vice Comptroller Donna Landries

36:10.365 --> 36:13.200
of that fateful day
back in October of 1964

36:13.234 --> 36:14.801
in Sandusky, Ohio,

36:14.836 --> 36:16.703
when she attended the circus

36:16.738 --> 36:18.872
and witnessed the most notorious

36:18.906 --> 36:23.043
mass clown stomping in the
history of elephant husbandry.

36:23.077 --> 36:25.278
I included a song from Starship

36:25.313 --> 36:26.847
to subconsciously

36:26.881 --> 36:28.682
unsettle Rod Remington,

36:28.716 --> 36:31.318
who was briefly in
an acrimonious group marriage

36:31.352 --> 36:34.221
with all seven members
of Jefferson Airplane.

36:34.255 --> 36:35.789
But what about the dog trainer?

36:35.823 --> 36:37.958
That chick's rocking an IQ
in the low 80s.

36:37.992 --> 36:39.860
She's an actual idiot.

36:39.894 --> 36:41.628
She was always gonna
love you people.

36:41.663 --> 36:43.563
Well, then why did you
put eyedrops

36:43.598 --> 36:45.032
in the McKinley water system?

36:45.066 --> 36:46.633
I mean, why did you
want the glee club

36:46.668 --> 36:48.168
to spend an entire day

36:48.202 --> 36:50.404
violently projectile-vomiting?
Well, I figured

36:50.438 --> 36:52.506
they all needed to lose
a few pounds, and there's

36:52.540 --> 36:55.475
nothing like a day-long
projectile-vomiting sesh

36:55.510 --> 36:57.411
to jump-start
the old metabolism.

36:57.445 --> 36:59.046
Then why the glitter bombs?

36:59.080 --> 37:02.416
Well, that was to trigger
the stress hormone cortisol.

37:02.450 --> 37:04.718
A good burst of cortisol
boosts alertness

37:04.752 --> 37:07.254
and takes about three days
to fully exit the system,

37:07.288 --> 37:10.490
giving your glee club a
perfectly timed sensation

37:10.525 --> 37:13.393
of relaxed euphoria
the exact moment

37:13.428 --> 37:16.096
they walked onstage.

37:16.130 --> 37:17.831
Wow.

37:17.865 --> 37:19.099
Yeah.

37:19.133 --> 37:20.267
But why did you blow up my car?

37:20.301 --> 37:23.036
Well, that was just for fun.

37:24.739 --> 37:26.273
Well, Susan...

37:26.307 --> 37:28.275
William.

37:28.309 --> 37:29.843
Looks like this is it.

37:29.877 --> 37:31.645
Yeah.

37:38.386 --> 37:40.420
Wow. No thank-you?

37:42.156 --> 37:43.557
No thank-you for the person

37:43.591 --> 37:45.025
who just described
in painstaking detail

37:45.059 --> 37:46.860
how she sacrificed
her own well-being

37:46.894 --> 37:48.795
to save your glee club

37:48.830 --> 37:51.064
and guarantee your job
indefinitely?

37:51.099 --> 37:53.367
Mmm...

37:53.401 --> 37:54.601
Okay.

37:54.636 --> 37:56.770
Change of plans, Butt Chin.

37:56.804 --> 37:58.772
I'm gonna take the weekend,

37:58.806 --> 38:02.109
maybe fly down to my condo
in Boca, brown up a bit,

38:02.143 --> 38:04.945
and when I come back,
I will have come up

38:04.979 --> 38:08.015
with some brand-new ways
to destroy you.

38:10.685 --> 38:12.953
(sighs)

38:25.533 --> 38:28.001
(laughing)

38:28.036 --> 38:30.938
Looks like it was another
cutthroat sectionals.

38:30.972 --> 38:34.007
You know, I forgot the way
it smells in here.

38:34.042 --> 38:37.311
All that life-or-death
teen adrenaline, all that drama.

38:37.345 --> 38:39.580
Feels like a million years ago.

38:39.614 --> 38:41.348
Miss it that much, huh?

38:41.382 --> 38:43.817
(laughs) Oh, God, yes.

38:43.851 --> 38:46.853
Give me a medley or a mash-up
or a Broadway tribute,

38:46.888 --> 38:49.022
anything to get me
back up on that stage

38:49.057 --> 38:52.359
with my friends, singing
and dancing for my life.

38:52.393 --> 38:55.462
God, I loved it so much.

38:55.496 --> 38:57.831
But you know what?

38:59.167 --> 39:01.301
We got bigger fish
to fry now, Berry.

39:01.336 --> 39:03.670
You, me, the footlights
of Broadway.

39:03.705 --> 39:04.838
I don't know

39:04.873 --> 39:06.473
if you've found an apartment yet

39:06.507 --> 39:09.009
to live in,
in New York, but, uh,

39:09.043 --> 39:11.345
you can always stay at mine
until you find one.

39:11.379 --> 39:14.514
No strings attached, of course.

39:14.549 --> 39:16.049
He said flirtatiously.

39:17.318 --> 39:19.219
I turned down the part,

39:19.254 --> 39:20.554
and I decided

39:20.588 --> 39:22.389
to go back to NYADA.

39:22.423 --> 39:24.558
I think I was afraid that going

39:24.592 --> 39:27.528
back to college would be
a step backwards, but...

39:29.531 --> 39:31.565
I think it's a step
in the right direction.

39:31.599 --> 39:33.000
- Hmm.
- So...

39:33.034 --> 39:34.568
don't be mad.

39:34.602 --> 39:36.470
- You're mad.
- No.

39:36.504 --> 39:38.639
I'm not mad.

39:38.673 --> 39:40.908
Sad that I won't be spending

39:40.942 --> 39:43.243
every night onstage
with Rachel Berry, absolutely,

39:43.278 --> 39:44.878
but I'm proud of you.

39:44.913 --> 39:46.480
You went with your gut.

39:46.514 --> 39:49.149
You didn't take the easy
road back to Broadway.

39:49.184 --> 39:50.851
And you know what I think?

39:50.885 --> 39:53.387
NYADA better watch out,
'cause the Berry is back.

39:53.421 --> 39:55.923
(chuckles softly)

39:55.957 --> 39:57.324
(sighs)

39:57.358 --> 39:59.426
Thank you so much
for understanding.

39:59.460 --> 40:01.595
And I will be there on
your opening night,

40:01.629 --> 40:03.363
so you better not screw up,
because I'll have an egg

40:03.398 --> 40:05.365
- in my purse with your name on it.
- Oh, wow.

40:05.400 --> 40:07.234
You're really not gonna let me
live that down, are you?

40:07.268 --> 40:08.602
- No.
- Well, maybe I can make it up

40:08.636 --> 40:10.170
to you, because,
you know, you're gonna

40:10.205 --> 40:12.239
be in New York,
and I'm gonna be in New York,

40:12.273 --> 40:13.707
so we're bound to run
into each other.

40:13.741 --> 40:14.942
I mean, we're bound to, yeah.

40:14.976 --> 40:16.877
I mean, I think it's inevitable.

40:16.911 --> 40:19.613
I'd like that.

40:29.824 --> 40:31.625
All right, I'm gonna go.

40:31.659 --> 40:33.660
I'll see you soon.

40:38.166 --> 40:40.267
(school bell ringing)

40:40.301 --> 40:41.635
(whooping and cheering)

40:41.669 --> 40:43.403
All right, the next
first-place trophy

40:43.438 --> 40:44.905
in that case
is gonna be regionals.

40:44.939 --> 40:47.908
(cheering)

40:47.942 --> 40:49.243
You know, someday... five,

40:49.277 --> 40:50.544
ten, 20 years from now...

40:50.578 --> 40:52.212
You're gonna walk
into this school

40:52.247 --> 40:54.248
and you're gonna see the
trophies in that case or...

40:54.282 --> 40:55.716
or maybe you'll be
watching your own

40:55.750 --> 40:57.384
sons and daughters
win their awards,

40:57.418 --> 41:00.654
and I hope you'll remember
this time in your life,

41:00.688 --> 41:02.556
this incredible
moment when a group

41:02.590 --> 41:05.325
of very different people
put aside their differences,

41:05.360 --> 41:07.928
supported each other
and formed a team,

41:07.962 --> 41:10.731
and hopefully made
some lifelong friendships.

41:10.765 --> 41:12.499
Now, some of our advisors

41:12.534 --> 41:15.135
are gonna be leaving us,

41:15.170 --> 41:17.671
but no matter where we go,
no matter where we are,

41:17.705 --> 41:19.173
we will always be
here in spirit,

41:19.207 --> 41:21.175
and we will always
be supporting you.

41:21.209 --> 41:23.610
Now, a chapter
in Glee Club history

41:23.645 --> 41:27.080
may be ending,
but it is just the beginning

41:27.115 --> 41:29.082
for all of you.

41:29.117 --> 41:30.784
We could not be
more proud of you.

41:30.819 --> 41:32.753
(whooping) Congratulations.

41:32.787 --> 41:35.088
Hey, let's hear it for
Rachel, Mr. Shue, Kurt

41:35.123 --> 41:36.590
and Blaine, everybody.
Oh...

41:36.624 --> 41:39.593
(cheering)

41:39.627 --> 41:42.129
(students murmuring)

41:51.539 --> 41:54.374
You know,
our two little trophies

41:54.409 --> 41:57.644
look really pathetic
in there all by themselves.

41:57.679 --> 42:00.547
I vote we get the old ones

42:00.582 --> 42:02.783
and put them back
in there with them.

42:02.817 --> 42:04.918
(others murmuring in agreement)

42:15.263 --> 42:17.831
(laughter)

42:26.040 --> 42:28.575
(cheering)

42:31.946 --> 42:33.680
WILL:
<i>Congratulations, guys.</i>

42:33.715 --> 42:35.716
(cheering)

42:39.854 --> 42:41.622
(cheering and applause)

42:55.136 --> 42:57.805
(applause)

